eneration.\n\n</objective>\n\n<context>\n\nRead `/workspace/specs/in-progress/001-scanner-auto-inject-flag.md` AC4 and AC5 sections for the exact probe procedures. This prompt is the procedural execution of those ACs.\nRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/git-workflow.md` for the buca workflow and branch model.\nThe probe uses the vault worktree at `~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal` (per AC4 step 1 and AC5 evidence). Verify this directory exists and contains a git worktree pointed at the shared `obsidian-personal.git` remote before running the probe. If the directory is missing, report in `## Improvements` (category: PROMPT) — the probe cannot run from this YOLO container.\n\nThis prompt assumes the operator (NOT the YOLO container) executes it. The YOLO container is forbidden from touching `~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal` directly (per `~/.claude-yolo/CLAUDE.md` rules: no kubectl in containers, no production credential access). The YOLO generates this prompt; the management session (or human operator) runs the verification.\n\n</context>\n\n<requirements>\n\n1. **Pre-conditions (operator must confirm before running AC4):**\n   - Prompts 1 and 2 merged to `master` on `agent-task-controller` repo.\n   - `cd ~/Documents/workspaces/agent-dev && git pull && git merge master` succeeded.\n   - `cd task/controller && BRANCH=dev make buca` succeeded (image built and rolled out to the dev STS).\n   - `kubectlquant -n dev describe deploy agent-task-controller | grep Image` shows the new image SHA matching the merge commit.\n   - `kubectlquant -n dev describe pod -l app=agent-task-controller | grep AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER` shows `value: false` (the env var must be set on the dev STS by the companion `bborbe/quant` commit). If the env var is unset, the pod will be in `CrashLoopBackOff` — STOP and report (per the AC1 failure mode).\n\n2. **AC4 probe procedure (dev, flag=false):**\n   ```\n   cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal\n   TS=$(date +%s)\n   touch \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n   cat > \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\" <<EOF\n   ---\n   page_type: task\n   status: in_progress\n   ---\n   # test probe\n   EOF\n   git add \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n   git commit -m \"test: scanner-flag probe ${TS}\"\n   git push origin master\n   ```\n   - Wait 60 seconds for one scanner poll cycle (the controller polls on `POLL_INTERVAL`, default 60s).\n   - Capture evidence BEFORE cleanup:\n     ```\n     kubectlquant -n dev logs -l app=agent-task-controller --tail=200 | grep 'AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER=false; skipping task without valid task_identifier: _test-probe-'\n     ```\n   - AC4 asserts ≥1 matching line referencing the probe file's `relPath`. If zero matches, AC4 fails.\n   - Mandatory cleanup (probe files left in the vault WILL cause real work to be picked up by the partner replica):\n     ```\n     rm \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n     git add -u\n     git commit -m \"test: cleanup scanner-flag probe ${TS}\"\n     git push origin master\n     ```\n\n3. **AC5 pre-conditions (operator must confirm before running AC5):**\n   - AC4 passed.\n   - The companion commit in `bborbe/quant` is merged and rolled out: the prod STS has `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER=true` env var set, dev STS has `false`. Verify via:\n     ```\n     kubectlquant -n prod describe pod -l app=agent-task-controller | grep AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\n     kubectlquant -n dev  describe pod -l app=agent-task-controller | grep AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\n     ```\n     Both should show `value: true` (prod) and `value: false` (dev).\n   - `cd ~/Documents/workspaces/agent-prod && git pull && git merge master` succeeded.\n   - `cd task/controller && BRANCH=prod make buca` succeeded.\n   - `kubectlquant -n prod describe deploy agent-task-controller | grep Image` shows the same new image SHA.\n\n4. **AC5 probe procedure (prod, flag=true):**\n   ```\n   cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal\n   TS=$(date +%s)\n   touch \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n   cat > \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\" <<EOF\n   ---\n   page_type: task\n   status: in_progress\n   ---\n   # test probe\n   EOF\n   git add \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n   git commit -m \"test: scanner-flag probe ${TS}\"\n   git push origin master\n   ```\n   - Wait 60 seconds for one scanner poll cycle.\n   - Capture evidence BEFORE cleanup (the order matters — if a race occurs during `rm`, the log line must already be captured):\n     ```\n     cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal && git log --since='5 minutes ago' --grep='git-rest: update' -- ':(glob)_test-probe-*.md'\n     ```\n     AC5 asserts this returns exactly ONE commit (from the prod pod; the dev pod's gate means it did NOT commit).\n     ```\n     grep '^task_identifier:' \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n     ```\n     AC5 asserts this returns one line with a UUID-shaped value (matches regex `^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-4[0-9a-f]{3}-[89ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$`).\n     ```\n     ls \"_conflicts/_test-probe-${TS}.md\" 2>/dev/null\n     ```\n     AC5 asserts this returns nothing. If the file appears, the race has recurred — STOP and report the AC as failed.\n   - Mandatory cleanup:\n     ```\n     rm \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n     git add -u\n     git commit -m \"test: cleanup scanner-flag probe ${TS}\"\n     git push origin master\n     ```\n   - If a `_conflicts/_test-probe-${TS}.md` file appeared during the probe, also `rm` it and flag AC5 as failed.\n\n5. **If AC4 or AC5 fails:**\n   - Do NOT attempt to \"fix\" by changing the code from this prompt. Report the failure to the dark-factory orchestrator (or human operator) with the captured log/git output.\n   - The likely root causes for AC4 failure: the env var was not set on the dev STS (companion `bborbe/quant` commit not merged or not rolled out); the gate helper is not actually emitting the warn log (regression in prompt 2); the `autoInject` field default is `true` instead of `false` when `SetAutoInject(false)` is not called (regression in prompt 1).\n   - The likely root causes for AC5 failure: the env var was not set on the prod STS (companion `bborbe/quant` commit not merged); two replicas are BOTH `true` (misconfig — the spec explicitly does not prevent this); the race is still happening for some other reason.\n\n6. **No code changes from this prompt.** This prompt is verification-only. It does not run `go generate`, `make precommit`, or modify any files in `/workspace`.\n\n7. **No scenario file is generated.** The spec's \"Scenario coverage: NO new scenario\" decision is honored — AC2/AC3/AC7 cover unit-level branch logic, AC4/AC5 cover end-to-end behavior. No `scenarios/NNN-*.md` file is written.\n\n</requirements>\n\n<constraints>\n\n- Spec Constraints #51–57 all apply (existing fixtures pass, factory signatures grow but don't lose parameters, frozen log substring, return shape `(nil, \"\", false)`, `.dark-factory.yaml` stays at `autoRelease: false`, no `CHANGELOG.md`).\n- Spec Failure Modes table — all rows are covered either by prompt 1 (envconfig error → CrashLoopBackOff), prompt 2 (skip path), or this prompt's AC4/AC5 evidence capture. The misconfig row (\"operator sets both replicas to `true`\") is explicitly out of scope for the spec (\"future spec (admission webhook) covers it\"); this prompt must NOT invent additional verification for it.\n- This prompt is NOT executed by the YOLO container. It is a runbook for the operator (or management session). The YOLO container does NOT have access to `~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal`, the dev/prod clusters, or the vault git remote.\n- Do NOT modify `.dark-factory.yaml` — spec Constraint #55 pins `autoRelease: false`.\n- Do NOT clean up the pre-existing `_conflicts/24 Tasks/...1782559254.md` files — that's a separate subtask (spec Non-goal #8).\n- Do NOT touch the `bborbe/quant` repo from this prompt. The companion commit there is a prerequisite, not part of this prompt's scope.\n\n</constraints>\n\n<verification>\n\nThis prompt's \"verification\" is the AC4 + AC5 probe execution itself. No automated tests run. If