{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_8wnb4ldxeox3_1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Three prompt files created. Note: the spec's Suggested Decomposition was 3 prompts; the dark-factory instructions say \"2-3 for single feature, 4-6 for major feature\" — this is a 3-prompt decomposition matching the spec exactly.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/workspace/prompts/001-spec-001-config-and-factory-wiring.md` — config + factory wiring + counterfeiter mock regen + AC1 tests\n- `/workspace/prompts/002-spec-001-scanner-gate-and-tests.md` — three-site gate + new `ReasonAutoInjectDisabled` counter + AC2/AC3/AC7 tests\n- `/workspace/prompts/003-spec-001-post-deploy-verification.md` — operator runbook for AC4/AC5 (no code changes)\n\n**Execution order:** 1 → 2 → 3. Prompt 2 depends on prompt 1 (the `autoInject` field, `SetAutoInject` setter, and regenerated counterfeiter mock must exist). Prompt 3 depends on prompts 1 and 2 being merged to master AND the companion `bborbe/quant` commit landing env vars on both STS replicas.\n\n**Key constraints repeated in every prompt:**\n- Spec Non-goals #1 (no default), #4 (no git-rest changes), #9 (no CHANGELOG.md)\n- Spec Constraints #51 (existing fixtures pass when flag=true), #53 (frozen log substring), #54 (skip return shape `(nil, \"\", false)`)\n- Do NOT commit (dark-factory handles git)\n- Use `bborbe/argument` library patterns, never `fmt.Errorf`, errors via `errors.Errorf(ctx, ...)`\n\n**Key design decisions (surfaced inside the prompts, not as questions to the user):**\n\n1. **Boolean env var trap avoided.** The `bborbe/argument` library's `validateRequiredField` (`/home/node/go/pkg/mod/github.com/bborbe/argument/v2@v2.12.27/argument_validate.go:110`) treats `case bool:` as empty — a `required:\"true\"` bool always passes validation, because Go's zero value (`false`) silently masks the unset env. The spec's AC1 (\"process refuses to start if unset\") is unmet by a naive `bool` declaration. Prompt 1 declares `AutoInjectTaskIdentifier` as `string`, parses to bool via `strconv.ParseBool` inside `Run()`, and surfaces the raw string in error messages. Prompt 1 step 7's `main_internal_test.go` test pins `f.Type.Kind() == reflect.String` to block regression to bool.\n\n2. **`SetAutoInject` added to the public interface, not the constructors.** Adding a new required parameter to `NewVaultScanner`/`NewGitRestVaultScanner` would force prompt 1 to also modify `vault_scanner_test.go` and `vault_scanner_internal_test.go` (every `&vaultScanner{...}` literal would need a new value). Instead, prompt 1 adds `SetAutoInject(enabled bool)` to the `VaultScanner` interface, defaulting the field to `true` in the existing constructors so existing tests pass unchanged.\n\n3. **`newVaultScannerWithAutoInject` was rejected** during design — pkg-private constructors across packages don't work in Go. The chosen pattern (interface method + factory call) keeps the factory zero-logic per `go-factory-pattern.md`.\n\n4. **Parity-check test invariant (line 1035–1058 of `vault_scanner_test.go`) updated.** The existing test asserts `skipCount == 6 && counterCount == 6`. Adding three new gated-skip sites with shared helper bumps both to 9. Prompt 2 explicitly updates this constant — it's the kind of test that's easy to overlook.\n\n5. **All existing `&vaultScanner{...}` literals get `autoInject: true`.** This is a prompt-2 task explicitly listed in step 6; without it, every existing inject test (line 661, 679, 700, 727) would silently fail because the scanner would be in gate-off mode by Go's zero-value default.\n\n6. **No scenario prompt emitted.** The spec explicitly says \"Scenario coverage: NO new scenario\" — `docs/rules/scenario-writing.md` doesn't exist on disk, and the spec's own decision is honored.\n\n**Docs referenced (in-container path):**\n- `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-patterns.md`\n- `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-factory-pattern.md`\n- `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-testing-guide.md`\n- `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-error-wrapping-guide.md`\n- `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-precommit.md`\n- `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/git-workflow.md`\n\n**Open questions surfaced inside prompts (not blocking):**\n- Prompt 2 step 9 notes that the project has no existing glog-capture pattern and the agent must `grep` the installed `golang/glog` version to discover the correct redirect API (`SetOutput` vs `LogToStderr` + `os.Pipe`). A fallback (assert the `ReasonAutoInjectDisabled` counter instead of log substring) is documented.\n- Prompt 2 step 11 notes that prompt 1's counterfeiter regen is a prerequisite; if prompt 1 was skipped, the mock at `/workspace/mocks/vault_scanner.go` would be stale.\n\n**Suggestion:** Run `/audit-prompt /workspace/prompts/001-spec-001-config-and-factory-wiring.md` (and 002, 003) to validate before approving."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a87f7a3220a9e6330 (use SendMessage with to: 'a87f7a3220a9e6330' to continue this agent)\n<usage>subagent_tokens: 65451\ntool_uses: 58\nduration_ms: 200163</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"213d66d0-dce3-49f1-a7b2-16c36173f959","uuid":"22cce8ee-d33f-4f1c-b81e-d624fcc5dec1","timestamp":"2026-06-27T21:33:11.675Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the spec file at `/workspace/Users/bborbe/Documents/workspaces/agent-task-controller-scanner-flag/specs/in-progress/001-scanner-auto-inject-flag.md` and generate dark-factory prompt files from it.\n\nOutput directory: `/workspace/prompts/` (inbox — not `prompts/in-progress/`)\nMode: non-interactive\n\nThe agent has full access to `/workspace/` for reading source files to verify signatures, look up library APIs, and discover existing patterns. It MUST do so before writing requirements.\n\nFollow the prompt-creator workflow: read the spec, understand the requirements, decide how many prompts to produce (1 for config change, 2-3 for single feature, 4-6 for major feature), generate the prompt files with proper naming (1-, 2-, 3- prefixes for execution order), then return a summary of what was created, key decisions made, and any open questions that were surfaced.\n\nDO NOT call AskUserQuestion. Resolve any ambiguity from the spec content itself — if genuinely under-specified, produce best-effort decomposition and surface open questions as comments inside the generated prompts.","agentId":"a87f7a3220a9e6330","agentType":"dark-factory:prompt-creator","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Three prompt files created. Note: the spec's Suggested Decomposition was 3 prompts; the dark-factory instructions say \"2-3 for single feature, 4-6 for major feature\" — this is a 3-prompt decomposition matching the spec exactly.\n\n## Summary\n\n**Files created:**\n- `/workspace/prompts/001-spec-001-config-and-factory-wiring.md` — config + factory wiring + counterfeiter mock regen + AC1 tests\n- `/workspace/prompts/002-spec-001-scanner-gate-and-tests.md` — three-site gate + new `ReasonAutoInjectDisabled` counter + AC2/AC3/AC7 tests\n- `/workspace/prompts/003-spec-001-post-deploy-verification.md` — operator runbook for AC4/AC5 (no code changes)\n\n**Execution order:** 1 → 2 → 3. Prompt 2 depends on prompt 1 (the `autoInject` field, `SetAutoInject` setter, and regenerated counterfeiter mock must exist). Prompt 3 depends on prompts 1 and 2 being merged to master AND the companion `bborbe/quant` commit landing env vars on both STS replicas.\n\n**Key constraints repeated in every prompt:**\n- Spec Non-goals #1 (no default), #4 (no git-rest changes), #9 (no CHANGELOG.md)\n- Spec Constraints #51 (existing fixtures pass when flag=true), #53 (frozen log substring), #54 (skip return shape `(nil, \"\", false)`)\n- Do NOT commit (dark-factory handles git)\n- Use `bborbe/argument` library patterns, never `fmt.Errorf`, er