. **Add the required env field to `application` in `/workspace/main.go`.**\n42\t   - Field name: `AutoInjectTaskIdentifier string`.\n43\t   - Field type: `string` (NOT `bool` — see context for why `required:\"true\"` on bool is silently bypassed).\n44\t   - Struct tags (preserving alignment style of the surrounding fields):\n45\t     ```\n46\t     AutoInjectTaskIdentifier string `required:\"true\"  arg:\"auto-inject-task-identifier\" env:\"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\" usage:\"allow this replica to backfill missing/invalid task_identifier fields (set true on exactly one replica per shared vault; false on all others); required\"`\n47\t     ```\n48\t   - Place the field after `VaultName` (last field in the current struct) to keep config-grouping clean.\n49\t   - Do NOT add a `default:` tag. The spec Non-goal #1 forbids it.\n50\t\n51\t2. **Parse and validate the field at the start of `Run()` in `/workspace/main.go`.**\n52\t   - Immediately after `routing.ValidateVaultName(...)` (line 68) and BEFORE `libmetrics.NewBuildInfoMetrics().SetBuildInfo(...)` (line 71), add:\n53\t     ```go\n54\t     autoInject, err := strconv.ParseBool(a.AutoInjectTaskIdentifier)\n55\t     if err != nil {\n56\t         return errors.Errorf(\n57\t             ctx,\n58\t             \"AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER must be parseable as bool (true/false), got %q\",\n59\t             a.AutoInjectTaskIdentifier,\n60\t         )\n61\t     }\n62\t     ```\n63\t   - Add `\"strconv\"` to the imports block if not already present.\n64\t   - The existing `errors.Errorf` import is already present — use it (per `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-error-wrapping-guide.md`, never use `fmt.Errorf` in `pkg/`-style code).\n65\t\n66\t3. **Add a factory function in `/workspace/pkg/factory/factory.go` that constructs the vault scanner with the flag plumbed in.**\n67\t   - Function signature:\n68\t     ```go\n69\t     func CreateVaultScanner(\n70\t         gitClient gitclient.GitClient,\n71\t         taskDir string,\n72\t         pollInterval time.Duration,\n73\t         trigger <-chan struct{},\n74\t         m metrics.Metrics,\n75\t         autoInject bool,\n76\t     ) scanner.VaultScanner\n77\t     ```\n78\t   - Import paths (add to the import block):\n79\t     - `\"time\"` (stdlib)\n80\t     - `\"github.com/bborbe/agent-task-controller/pkg/metrics\"`\n81\t     - `\"github.com/bborbe/agent-task-controller/pkg/scanner\"`\n82\t   - Body: thin wrapper — call `scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner(gitClient, taskDir, pollInterval, trigger, m)` and set `autoInject: autoInject` on the returned struct via type assertion. The factory has zero business logic per `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-factory-pattern.md`.\n83\t   - Implementation note: since `vaultScanner` is unexported and `NewGitRestVaultScanner` returns the `VaultScanner` interface, the factory cannot directly set the private `autoInject` field. Either:\n84\t     - (a) Expose a package-private `WithAutoInject` setter in `pkg/scanner/` (low-risk: package-private, scoped to tests + factory), OR\n85\t     - (b) Add a private-package constructor `newVaultScannerWithAutoInject(...)` that takes the flag and call that from the factory.\n86\t   - Pick option (b): it keeps the public `NewGitRestVaultScanner` signature unchanged (preserving the existing `vault_scanner_test.go` and `vault_scanner_internal_test.go` fixtures that pass `nil` for the trigger channel — adding a new required parameter to the public function would break them and force prompt 1 to also touch test files, which violates the spec's \"config + factory wiring\" scope).\n87\t   - Concrete shape:\n88\t     ```go\n89\t     func newVaultScannerWithAutoInject(\n90\t         gitClient gitclient.GitClient,\n91\t         taskDir string,\n92\t         pollInterval time.Duration,\n93\t         trigger <-chan struct{},\n94\t         m metrics.Metrics,\n95\t         autoInject bool,\n96\t     ) scanner.VaultScanner {\n97\t         return scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner(gitClient, taskDir, pollInterval, trigger, m) //nolint:staticcheck // see test coverage\n98\t     }\n99\t     ```\n100\t     But this returns a `VaultScanner` interface, not a `*vaultScanner`. So **instead, do this in `pkg/scanner/`** (not in `pkg/factory/`):\n101\t     - In `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner.go`, add a private constructor `newVaultScannerWithAutoInject` that returns `*vaultScanner` (the concrete type). Place it next to `NewVaultScanner`/`NewGitRestVaultScanner`.\n102\t     - The factory in `pkg/factory/` then calls this private constructor — but it can't, because it's in a different package.\n103\t   - **Revised correct shape**: The factory does the wiring by calling `NewGitRestVaultScanner` and then exposing a setter. Add a new exported method to `VaultScanner` interface in `pkg/scanner/vault_scanner.go`:\n104\t     ```go\n105\t     type VaultScanner interface {\n106\t         Run(ctx context.Context, results chan<- ScanResult) error\n107\t         RunCycle(ctx context.Context, results chan<- ScanResult)\n108\t         SetAutoInject(enabled bool)\n109\t     }\n110\t     ```\n111\t     Add the method on `*vaultScanner` (assigns `v.autoInject = enabled`). Regenerate the counterfeiter mock at `/workspace/mocks/vault_scanner.go` via `go generate ./pkg/scanner/...` (the existing `//counterfeiter:generate -o ../../mocks/vault_scanner.go --fake-name VaultScanner . VaultScanner` directive will pick it up).\n112\t   - **Why this shape**: it preserves all existing callers (`NewVaultScanner`, `NewGitRestVaultScanner` keep their signatures; existing tests don't need to change), and lets the factory set the flag post-construction.\n113\t   - The factory body becomes:\n114\t     ```go\n115\t     func CreateVaultScanner(\n116\t         gitClient gitclient.GitClient,\n117\t         taskDir string,\n118\t         pollInterval time.Duration,\n119\t         trigger <-chan struct{},\n120\t         m metrics.Metrics,\n121\t         autoInject bool,\n122\t     ) scanner.VaultScanner {\n123\t         vs := scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner(gitClient, taskDir, pollInterval, trigger, m)\n124\t         vs.SetAutoInject(autoInject)\n125\t         return vs\n126\t     }\n127\t     ```\n128\t\n129\t4. **Add the private `autoInject` field to `vaultScanner` in `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner.go`.**\n130\t   - Add `autoInject bool` as a new field on the `vaultScanner` struct (after `ops fileOps` at line 61).\n131\t   - Initialize it to `true` in BOTH `NewVaultScanner` (line 105) and `NewGitRestVaultScanner` (line 126). Default `true` is critical — it preserves today's behavior for all existing test fixtures and any external callers (the parity regression bar).\n132\t   - Add the `SetAutoInject` method on `*vaultScanner`:\n133\t     ```go\n134\t     func (v *vaultScanner) SetAutoInject(enabled bool) {\n135\t         v.autoInject = enabled\n136\t     }\n137\t     ```\n138\t\n139\t5. **Regenerate the counterfeiter mock.**\n140\t   - Run `cd /workspace && go generate ./pkg/scanner/...`.\n141\t   - This regenerates `/workspace/mocks/vault_scanner.go` with a `SetAutoInject` no-op method on the fake.\n142\t   - Verify `/workspace/mocks/vault_scanner.go` now contains `func (fake *VaultScanner) SetAutoInject(enabled bool)` (or equivalent).\n143\t\n144\t6. **Replace the direct scanner construction in `/workspace/main.go` (line 106).**\n145\t   - Replace `scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner(...)` at line 106 with `factory.CreateVaultScanner(..., autoInject)`.\n146\t   - Pass the locally-parsed `autoInject` bool (from step 2) as the last argument.\n147\t   - The five existing arguments (`gitClient`, `a.TaskDir`, `a.PollInterval`, `trigger`, `metrics.New()`) stay in the same order. Adding `autoInject` at the end is non-breaking.\n148\t\n149\t7. **Add a unit test that asserts `AutoInjectTaskIdentifier` is wired with the required tag.**\n150\t   - File: `/workspace/main_internal_test.go` (append, do NOT modify existing tests