nner_test.go` lines 1035–1058. It asserts `skipCount == 6` and `counterCount == 6`. After this prompt adds three new \"skipping\" warn lines AND three matching `SkippedFilesTotal(...)` calls, the counts both become 9. The test's `skipCount` regex (`glog.Warningf(\"skipping`) / `glog.Errorf(\"skipping`) / `glog.Warningf(\"failed to read`) ) MUST be updated to expect 9.\n32\t\n33\t</context>\n34\t\n35\t<requirements>\n36\t\n37\t1. **Add the new reason constant in `/workspace/pkg/metrics/metrics.go`.**\n38\t   - In the `const ( ... )` block at line 147, add `ReasonAutoInjectDisabled = \"auto_inject_disabled\"` as a new entry.\n39\t   - In the `init()` loop at lines 201–208 that pre-initializes counters, add `ReasonAutoInjectDisabled` to the slice so `prometheus.DefaultGatherer` exposes it from boot.\n40\t   - Update the package doc comment on `SkippedFilesTotal` (line 159) to mention \"auto-inject disabled\" as a labeled reason — minor edit, not load-bearing.\n41\t\n42\t2. **Gate the three injection trigger sites in `/workspace/pkg/scanner/vault_scanner.go`.**\n43\t   - The three sites are at lines 261 (empty `taskID`), 264 (non-UUID), 268 (duplicate UUID). Currently they are:\n44\t     ```go\n45\t     if taskID == \"\" {\n46\t         return v.injectAndStore(ctx, content, relPath, currentFMAssignee)\n47\t     }\n48\t     if !isValidUUID(taskID) {\n49\t         glog.Warningf(\"replacing non-UUID task_identifier %q in %s\", taskID, relPath)\n50\t         return v.injectAndStore(ctx, removeTaskIdentifier(content), relPath, currentFMAssignee)\n51\t     }\n52\t     if !v.isIdentifierUnique(taskID, relPath) {\n53\t         glog.Warningf(\"replacing duplicate task_identifier %q in %s\", taskID, relPath)\n54\t         return v.injectAndStore(ctx, removeTaskIdentifier(content), relPath, currentFMAssignee)\n55\t     }\n56\t     ```\n57\t   - Wrap each `return v.injectAndStore(...)` so that when `v.autoInject == false`, the call is replaced with a gate:\n58\t     ```go\n59\t    