{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_5UYrbV7NmlgwL3r6gy1TDOBI","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tspec: [\"001\"]\n3\tstatus: draft\n4\tcreated: \"2026-06-27T21:30:00Z\"\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\t<summary>\n8\t\n9\t- After prompts 1 and 2 merge and the operator runs `BRANCH=dev make buca`, the dev replica's `kubectl logs` will show the frozen-substring warn line for any UUID-less task file dropped into the shared vault.\n10\t- This prompt is the manual post-deploy verification step (AC4 and AC5) — it does NOT change code; it instructs the operator to run probe procedures against the live cluster.\n11\t- The dev probe (AC4) drops a UUID-less task file, waits 60s, greps the dev pod's logs for the gate substring, then cleans up the probe file via `rm && git commit && git push`.\n12\t- The prod probe (AC5) does the same but additionally verifies the file ends up with a UUID injected by the prod pod (`grep '^task_identifier:'` returns one UUID-shaped line) and no `_conflicts/_test-probe-*.md` file appears.\n13\t- AC5 depends on a same-day companion commit in `bborbe/quant` that sets `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER=true` on the prod STS and `false` on the dev STS — without that commit, the prod pod will crash on rolling update (per the AC1 failure mode).\n14\t- This prompt is the LAST in the sequence; it cannot run until prompts 1 and 2 are merged to master and the image is rebuilt + rolled out via `make buca`.\n15\t\n16\t</summary>\n17\t\n18\t<objective>\n19\t\n20\tVerify the end-to-end behavior of the gated scanner on real infrastructure. AC4 proves the dev replica (with `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER=false`) skips UUID-less files and emits the frozen-substring warn log. AC5 proves the prod replica (with `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER=true`) successfully injects a UUID and does NOT cause a `_conflicts/` quarantine. This is operator-driven verification, not code generation.\n21\t\n22\t</objective>\n23\t\n24\t<context>\n25\t\n26\tRead `/workspace/specs/in-progress/001-scanner-auto-inject-flag.md` AC4 and AC5 sections for the exact probe procedures. This prompt is the procedural execution of those ACs.\n27\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/git-workflow.md` for the buca workflow and branch model.\n28\tThe probe uses the vault worktree at `~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal` (per AC4 step 1 and AC5 evidence). Verify this directory exists and contains a git worktree pointed at the shared `obsidian-personal.git` remote before running the probe. If the directory is missing, report in `## Improvements` (category: PROMPT) — the probe cannot run from this YOLO container.\n29\t\n30\tThis prompt assumes the operator (NOT the YOLO container) executes it. The YOLO container is forbidden from touching `~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal` directly (per `~/.claude-yolo/CLAUDE.md` rules: no kubectl in containers, no production credential access). The YOLO generates this prompt; the management session (or human operator) runs the verification.\n31\t\n32\t</context>\n33\t\n34\t<requirements>\n35\t\n36\t1. **Pre-conditions (operator must confirm before running AC4):**\n37\t   - Prompts 1 and 2 merged to `master` on `agent-task-controller` repo.\n38\t   - `cd ~/Documents/workspaces/agent-dev && git pull && git merge master` succeeded.\n39\t   - `cd task/controller && BRANCH=dev make buca` succeeded (image built and rolled out to the dev STS).\n40\t   - `kubectlquant -n dev describe deploy agent-task-controller | grep Image` shows the new image SHA matching the merge commit.\n41\t   - `kubectlquant -n dev describe pod -l app=agent-task-controller | grep AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER` shows `value: false` (the env var must be set on the dev STS by the companion `bborbe/quant` commit). If the env var is unset, the pod will be in `CrashLoopBackOff` — STOP and report (per the AC1 failure mode).\n42\t\n43\t2. **AC4 probe procedure (dev, flag=false):**\n44\t   ```\n45\t   cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal\n46\t   TS=$(date +%s)\n47\t   touch \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n48\t   cat > \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\" <<EOF\n49\t   ---\n50\t   page_type: task\n51\t   status: in_progress\n52\t   ---\n53\t   # test probe\n54\t   EOF\n55\t   git add \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n56\t   git commit -m \"test: scanner-flag probe ${TS}\"\n57\t   git push origin master\n58\t   ```\n59\t   - Wait 60 seconds for one scanner poll cycle (the controller polls on `POLL_INTERVAL`, default 60s).\n60\t   - Capture evidence BEFORE cleanup:\n61\t     ```\n62\t     kubectlquant -n dev logs -l app=agent-task-controller --tail=200 | grep 'AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER=false; skipping task without valid task_identifier: _test-probe-'\n63\t     ```\n64\t   - AC4 asserts ≥1 matching line referencing the probe file's `relPath`. If zero matches, AC4 fails.\n65\t   - Mandatory cleanup (probe files left in the vault WILL cause real work to be picked up by the partner replica):\n66\t     ```\n67\t     rm \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n68\t     git add -u\n69\t     git commit -m \"test: cleanup scanner-flag probe ${TS}\"\n70\t     git push origin master\n71\t     ```\n72\t\n73\t3. **AC5 pre-conditions (operator must confirm before running AC5):**\n74\t   - AC4 passed.\n75\t   - The companion commit in `bborbe/quant` is merged and rolled out: the prod STS has `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER=true` env var set, dev STS has `false`. Verify via:\n76\t     ```\n77\t     kubectlquant -n prod describe pod -l app=agent-task-controller | grep AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\n78\t     kubectlquant -n dev  describe pod -l app=agent-task-controller | grep AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER\n79\t     ```\n80\t     Both should show `value: true` (prod) and `value: false` (dev).\n81\t   - `cd ~/Documents/workspaces/agent-prod && git pull && git merge master` succeeded.\n82\t   - `cd task/controller && BRANCH=prod make buca` succeeded.\n83\t   - `kubectlquant -n prod describe deploy agent-task-controller | grep Image` shows the same new image SHA.\n84\t\n85\t4. **AC5 probe procedure (prod, flag=true):**\n86\t   ```\n87\t   cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal\n88\t   TS=$(date +%s)\n89\t   touch \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n90\t   cat > \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\" <<EOF\n91\t   ---\n92\t   page_type: task\n93\t   status: in_progress\n94\t   ---\n95\t   # test probe\n96\t   EOF\n97\t   git add \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n98\t   git commit -m \"test: scanner-flag probe ${TS}\"\n99\t   git push origin master\n100\t   ```\n101\t   - Wait 60 seconds for one scanner poll cycle.\n102\t   - Capture evidence BEFORE cleanup (the order matters — if a race occurs during `rm`, the log line must already be captured):\n103\t     ```\n104\t     cd ~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal && git log --since='5 minutes ago' --grep='git-rest: update' -- ':(glob)_test-probe-*.md'\n105\t     ```\n106\t     AC5 asserts this returns exactly ONE commit (from the prod pod; the dev pod's gate means it did NOT commit).\n107\t     ```\n108\t     grep '^task_identifier:' \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n109\t     ```\n110\t     AC5 asserts this returns one line with a UUID-shaped value (matches regex `^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-4[0-9a-f]{3}-[89ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}$`).\n111\t     ```\n112\t     ls \"_conflicts/_test-probe-${TS}.md\" 2>/dev/null\n113\t     ```\n114\t     AC5 asserts this returns nothing. If the file appears, the race has recurred — STOP and report the AC as failed.\n115\t   - Mandatory cleanup:\n116\t     ```\n117\t     rm \"_test-probe-${TS}.md\"\n118\t     git add -u\n119\t     git commit -m \"test: cleanup scanner-flag probe ${TS}\"\n120\t     git push origin master\n121\t     ```\n122\t   - If a `_conflicts/_test-probe-${TS}.md` file appeared during the probe, also `rm` it and flag AC5 as failed.\n123\t\n124\t5. **If AC4 or AC5 fails:**\n125\t   - Do NOT attempt to \"fix\" by changing the code from this prompt. Report the failure to the dark-factory orchestrator (or human operator) with the captured log/git output.\n126\t   - The likely root causes for AC4 failure: the env var was not set on the dev STS (companion `bborbe/quant` commit not merged or not rolled out); the gate helper is not actually emitting the warn log (regression in prompt 2); the `autoInject` field default is `true` instead of `false` when `SetAutoInject(false)` is not called (regression in prompt 1).\n127\t   - The likely root causes for AC5 failure: the env var was not set on the prod STS (companion `bborbe/quant` commit not merged); two replicas are BOTH `true` (misconfig — the spec explicitly does not prevent this); the race is still happening for some other reason.\n128\t\n129\t6. **No code changes from this prompt.** This prompt is verification-only. It does not run `go generate`, `make precommit`, or modify any files in `/workspace`.\n130\t\n131\t7. **No scenario file is generated.** The spec's \"Scenario coverage: NO new scenario\" decision is honored — AC2/AC3/AC7 cover unit-level branch logic, AC4/AC5 cover end-to-end behavior. No `scenarios/NNN-*.md` file is written.\n132\t\n133\t</requirements>\n134\t\n135\t<constraints>\n136\t\n137\t- Spec Constraints #51–57 all apply (existing fixtures pass, factory signatures grow but don't lose parameters, frozen log substring, return shape `(nil, \"\", false)`, `.dark-factory.yaml` stays at `autoRelease: false`, no `CHANGELOG.md`).\n138\t- Spec Failure Modes table — all rows are covered either by prompt 1 (envconfig error → CrashLoopBackOff), prompt 2 (skip path), or this prompt's AC4/AC5 evidence capture. The misconfig row (\"operator sets both replicas to `true`\") is explicitly out of scope for the spec (\"future spec (admission webhook) covers it\"); this prompt must NOT invent additional verification for it.\n139\t- This prompt is NOT executed by the YOLO container. It is a runbook for the operator (or management session). The YOLO container does NOT have access to `~/Documents/Obsidian/Personal`, the dev/prod clusters, or the vault git remote.\n140\t- Do NOT modify `.dark-factory.yaml` — spec Constraint #55 pins `autoRelease: false`.\n141\t- Do NOT clean up the pre-existing `_conflicts/24 Tasks/...1782559254.md` files — that's a separate subtask (spec Non-goal #8).\n142\t- Do NOT touch the `bborbe/quant` repo from this prompt. The companion commit there is a prerequisite, not part of this prompt's scope.\n143\t\n144\t</constraints>\n145\t\n146\t<verification>\n147\t\n148\tThis prompt's \"verification\" is the AC4 + AC5 probe execution itself. No automated tests run. If AC4 and AC5 both pass, the spec is complete. If either fails, the operator must report the captured evidence (log lines, git log output, any `_conflicts/` files) to the dark-factory orchestrator.\n149\t\n150\tEvidence to attach to the completion report when AC4 + AC5 pass:\n151\t- AC4: the captured `kubectl logs | grep` line(s) for the probe `relPath`.\n152\t- AC5: the captured `git log --grep='git-rest: update'` output, the `grep '^task_identifier:'` output, and confirmation `ls _conflicts/_test-probe-*.md` returned nothing.\n153\t- Both: confirmation that both cleanup commits were pushed (no probe files remain in the vault).\n154\t\n155\t</verification>"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_gndwq2feccxh_3","session_id":"213d66d0-dce3-49f1-a7b2-16c36173f959","uuid":"15d0b714-b5b1-417d-bc6e-ac556cafb535","timestamp":"2026-06-27T21:33:29.262Z","subagent_type":"dark-factory:prompt-auditor","task_description":"Audit prompt 3"}
