{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_AVe9N0Er2B4v5aK1DK8RmpgA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tspec: [\"001\"]\n3\tstatus: draft\n4\tcreated: \"2026-06-27T21:30:00Z\"\n5\t---\n6\t\n7\t<summary>\n8\t\n9\t- The controller now refuses to start if `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER` is not set in the environment.\n10\t- A new required deployment-time env flag is added to the application config (no default value, no implicit zero).\n11\t- A new factory function in `pkg/factory/` constructs the vault scanner with the flag, replacing the direct `scanner.NewGitRestVaultScanner` call in `main.go`.\n12\t- The scanner gains a private `autoInject` boolean field that prompt 2 will gate the three injection trigger sites on.\n13\t- Existing required env vars (`LISTEN`, `KAFKA_BROKERS`, etc.) and all factory signatures for the command consumer remain unchanged.\n14\t- Existing scanner tests continue to pass without modification (they use `NewVaultScanner`/`NewGitRestVaultScanner` directly with no `autoInject` arg; this prompt makes the parameter optional by defaulting to `true` when callers omit it).\n15\t- No production behavior change at runtime when `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER=true` — parity is the regression bar.\n16\t</summary>\n17\t\n18\t<objective>\n19\t\n20\tIntroduce the required `AUTO_INJECT_TASK_IDENTIFIER` env flag into `application`, plumb it through a new factory function that constructs the vault scanner, and surface it on `vaultScanner` as a private boolean field. The flag must be required (no default), so a missing env var crashes the process before any scan runs. When set to `true`, behavior is identical to today; the gate logic is added by prompt 2.\n21\t\n22\t</objective>\n23\t\n24\t<context>\n25\t\n26\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-patterns.md` for interface + constructor + struct conventions.\n27\tRead `/home/node/.claude/plugins/marketplaces/coding/docs/go-factory-pattern.md` for `Create*