{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_TQz8lIl4L9mrhPNRMDlwctHN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# CLAUDE.md\n2\t\n3\t## Dark Factory Workflow\n4\t\n5\tThe headline reason to use prompts/specs: **safe unattended execution** in a YOLO Claude container with permission checks disabled. Queue work, step away, no \"approve this bash command?\" interruptions. Documentation, decomposition (specs only), and token savings (Sonnet vs Opus) follow as side benefits.\n6\t\n7\t### What to do\n8\t\n9\t1. **Choose a flow** — read [docs/choosing-a-flow.md](docs/choosing-a-flow.md). Single source of truth for direct vs prompt vs spec; do not duplicate the decision here. Default for markdown / docs / configs / small scripts is **direct edits, no dark-factory**.\n10\t\n11\t2. **Read the relevant guide before starting** — every time, not from memory:\n12\t   - Choosing direct vs prompt vs spec → read [docs/choosing-a-flow.md](docs/choosing-a-flow.md)\n13\t   - Architecture & flow → read [docs/architecture-flow.md](docs/architecture-flow.md)\n14\t   - Writing a spec → read [docs/spec-writing.md](docs/spec-writing.md)\n15\t   - Writing prompts → read [docs/prompt-writing.md](docs/prompt-writing.md)\n16\t   - Configuration → read [docs/configuration.md](docs/configuration.md)\n17\t   - Running prompts → read [docs/running.md](docs/running.md)\n18\t   - Running scenarios → read [docs/scenario-writing.md](docs/scenario-writing.md)\n19\t\n20\t3. **Follow the guide step by step.** Do not skip audit steps.\n21\t\n22\t4. **After completing a spec or major refactor**, run the relevant scenario to verify end-to-end behavior. Scenarios live in `scenarios/` (numbered by complexity). Always use a temp copy of the sandbox — never run against the original.\n23\t\n24\t5. **Before `make install`**, follow [docs/releasing-dark-factory.md](docs/releasing-dark-factory.md) — mandatory reading and procedure. The release gate (run all scenarios against a freshly built `/tmp/new-dark-factory`, NEVER the installed binary) and the version alignment check both live there. Unit tests + `make precommit` alone are not sufficient.\n25\t\n26\t   **Scenario-skip rule (only exception):** Compare installed version to HEAD — if no binary-relevant files changed, the installed binary is byte-equivalent to what you'd install, so scenarios add no signal.\n27\t   ```bash\n28\t   INSTALLED=$(dark-factory --version | awk '{print $2}')\n29\t   git diff $INSTALLED..HEAD --name-only | grep -E '\\.(go|mod|sum)$|^Makefile$|^Dockerfile$'\n30\t   # empty output → skip scenarios; any hit → run them\n31\t   ```\n32\t   Do NOT shortcut by \"change type\" intuition (\"docs-only\", \"pipeline-only\") — always run the diff.\n33\t\n34\t### Key rules (details in the guides)\n35\t\n36\t- Prompts go to **`prompts/`** (inbox) — never to `prompts/in-progress/` or `prompts/completed/`\n37\t- Specs go to **`specs/`** (inbox) — never to `specs/in-progress/` or `specs/completed/`\n38\t- Never number filenames — dark-factory assigns numbers on approve\n39\t- Never manually edit frontmatter status — use CLI:\n40\t  - `dark-factory prompt approve <name>` — queue prompt for execution\n41\t  - `dark-factory prompt retry` — re-queue failed prompts\n42\t  - `dark-factory spec approve <name>` — approve spec (triggers prompt generation)\n43\t  - `dark-factory spec complete <name>` — mark verified spec as completed\n44\t  - `dark-factory status` — show combined status\n45\t  - `dark-factory prompt list` / `dark-factory spec list` — list with status\n46\t- Always audit before approving (`/audit-prompt`, `/audit-spec`)\n47\t- Always verify before completing — use `/dark-factory:verify-spec <id>` over a manual `dark-factory spec complete`. The command refuses inspection-only \"evidence\" (logs, unit tests, old operational evidence, wire-level probes) and only marks complete after the scenario passes against fresh evidence\n48\t- **Never approve or run dark-factory without explicit user confirmation** — present the prompt, wait for user to say \"approve\" or \"run\"\n49\t- **Start daemon in background** — use Bash tool with `run_in_background: true`: `dark-factory daemon` (not foreground, not detached with `&`)\n50\t\n51\t## 🚨 Version Alignment — MANDATORY\n52\t\n53\t**Three plugin version strings MUST always equal each other:**\n54\t1. `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` — `\"version\"` field\n55\t2. `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` — `metadata.version`\n56\t3. `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` — `plugins[0].version`\n57\t\n58\t`make precommit` runs `check-versions` which fails the build if any of the three diverge. Never commit a plugin release with mismatched versions.\n59\t\n60\tThe binary version (CHANGELOG top entry + git tag) is a **separate stream** managed by the autoRelease daemon and is independent of the plugin version (per `docs/releasing-dark-factory.md`). The 3-way plugin alignment above is what `check-versions` enforces.\n61\t\n62\t## Plugin Release Checklist\n63\t\n64\t**When to release:** Any change to `commands/`, `agents/`, `docs/`, or `skills/` requires a plugin version bump — these files ship as part of the plugin.\n65\t\n66\t**How to release:**\n67\t\n68\t1. Pick the next version: increment minor from the latest `CHANGELOG.md` entry (e.g. v0.103.0 → v0.104.0)\n69\t2. Update **all four files** — version string must be identical everywhere (without `v` prefix in JSON):\n70\t   - `CHANGELOG.md` — add new `## vX.Y.Z` section at top with all changes (binary + plugin)\n71\t   - `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` — `\"version\": \"X.Y.Z\"`\n72\t   - `.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` — `\"version\": \"X.Y.Z\"` in **both** `metadata` and `plugins[0]`\n73\t3. Commit: `release plugin vX.Y.Z: <summary>`\n74\t4. Push: `git push`\n75\t\n76\t**Common mistakes:**\n77\t- Forgetting `.claude-plugin/` files (plugin stays at old version)\n78\t- Creating a separate \"Plugin vX\" changelog section (wrong — one version for everything)\n79\t- Using different versions in the 3 JSON fields (must all match)\n80\t- Not including binary changes (fetch timeout, lock fix) in the changelog when they're uncommitted\n81\t\n82\t## Useful Commands\n83\t\n84\t```bash\n85\t# Find all dark-factory projects\n86\tfind ~/Documents/workspaces -maxdepth 3 -type f -name \".dark-factory.yaml\" -not -path \"*/vendor/*\"\n87\t\n88\t# Add gitignore entry to all dark-factory projects\n89\t~/Documents/workspaces/scripts/gitignore-add-exclude.sh '/<entry>'\n90\t```\n91\t\n92\t## Development Standards\n93\t\n94\tThis project follows the [coding-guidelines](https://github.com/bborbe/coding-guidelines).\n95\t\n96\t### Key Reference Guides\n97\t\n98\t- **[go-architecture-patterns.md](~/Documents/workspaces/coding-guidelines/go-architecture-patterns.md)** - Interface → Constructor → Struct → Method\n99\t- **[go-testing-guide.md](~/Documents/workspaces/coding-guidelines/go-testing-guide.md)** - Ginkgo v2/Gomega testing\n100\t- **[go-makefile-commands.md](~/Documents/workspaces/coding-guidelines/go-makefile-commands.md)** - Build commands\n101\t- **[git-commit-workflow.md](~/Documents/workspaces/coding-guidelines/git-commit-workflow.md)** - Commit process\n102\t\n103\t## Architecture\n104\t\n105\t- `main.go` — CLI entry point, subcommands: `run`, `status`, `prompt approve/reset`\n106\t- `pkg/cmd/` — CLI subcommands (daemon, run, status, prompt, spec)\n107\t- `pkg/config/` — Configuration parsing (`.dark-factory.yaml`)\n108\t- `pkg/executor/` — Execute single prompt via claude-yolo Docker container\n109\t- `pkg/factory/` — Wire dependencies, create processor and review poller\n110\t- `pkg/generator/` — Auto-generate prompts from approved specs\n111\t- `pkg/git/` — Git operations: clone, branch, commit, push, PR creation, merge\n112\t- `pkg/lock/` — Instance lock (one dark-factory per project)\n113\t- `pkg/processor/` — Core orchestration: pick up prompts, setup workflow, execute, handle post-execution\n114\t- `pkg/project/` — Project metadata detection\n115\t- `pkg/prompt/` — Parse/update YAML frontmatter in prompt markdown files\n116\t- `pkg/report/` — Parse completion reports from YOLO output\n117\t- `pkg/review/` — PR review polling for autoReview mode\n118\t- `pkg/runner/` — Docker container lifecycle management\n119\t- `pkg/server/` — REST API for status and control\n120\t- `pkg/spec/` — Spec file management and auto-completion\n121\t- `pkg/specnum/` — Spec number assignment\n122\t- `pkg/specwatcher/` — Watch specs/ directory for file changes\n123\t- `pkg/status/` — Combined status reporting\n124\t- `pkg/version/` — Version detection and management\n125\t- `pkg/watcher/` — Watch prompts/ directory for file changes\n126\t\n127\t## Key Design Decisions\n128\t\n129\t- **Frontmatter = state** — no database, prompt file frontmatter tracks status\n130\t- **Two workflow modes:** `direct` (commit to current branch) and `pr` (clone → feature branch → PR)\n131\t- **YOLO has NO git access** — all git ops on host; clone mounted read-write for code only\n132\t- **Sequential processing** — one prompt at a time per project\n133\t- **Stop on failure** — never skip failed prompts\n134\t- **PR workflow: prompt lifecycle in original repo** — clone contains only code changes; prompt move/status updates happen in the original working directory\n135\t- **Stale clone recovery** — cloner removes existing dest dir before cloning to handle crashes\n136\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_function_gndwq2feccxh_3","session_id":"213d66d0-dce3-49f1-a7b2-16c36173f959","uuid":"6e856cd2-cd65-49b7-9744-1b9d8cc0375a","timestamp":"2026-06-27T21:34:04.026Z","subagent_type":"dark-factory:prompt-auditor","task_description":"Audit prompt 3"}
